A note on carriers. I have MountainView Carriers, MC-445921, off
our board for now. Their insurance certificate expired 2026-09-28
and until they send a renewed certificate of insurance we are not
tendering them anything. Do not let anybody talk you into loading
them off a promise. On our historical lane work into Harlan we have
run $4.65 to $4.75 per mile depending on weight and season, so the
$4.85 on this Ridgemont run reflects where the market sits right
now, not a number I pulled out of the air.

Everything else on the board is covered with carriers running
current authority and insurance. If you want to add stops for
October let me know early in the week and I will work them in
before the trucks are committed.

